    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Tournament Scrabble is a mental marathon. Over two or three days you might play 20+ games, each demanding deep focus on anagram-finding, board vision, and strategic calculation. Physical preparation matters as much as word knowledge — here's how top players keep their edge from Round 1 to the final game.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Hydration & Nutrition for Peak Performance</h2>

    <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
        <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2-3L</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Water per day</p></div>
        <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Every 2h</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Snack break</p></div>
        <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">No sugar</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avoid crashes</p></div>
        <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Protein</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Sustained energy</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>Dehydration causes concentration to drop sharply — even a 2% deficit impairs cognitive function. Sip water throughout games rather than gulping between rounds. Between rounds, eat slow-release snacks: almonds, bananas, oat bars, or dark chocolate.</p>

    <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
